17/12/2004
PARIS, France -- Expo 2008 organisers announced Thursday (16 December) that the world fair will take place in Zaragoza, Spain.
Thessaloniki, Greece, and Trieste, Italy, were the other candidates.
Thessaloniki lost to both Zaragoza and Trieste during two rounds of voting by the International Exhibitions Bureau.
(ANA, MPA - 16/12/04)
